  "prompt": "What's the definition of vote margin?",
  "response": "The term \"vote margin\" refers to the difference in the number of votes between two candidates or parties in an election. It is a measure of how many more votes the winning candidate or party received compared to their closest competitor. The vote margin can be expressed as an absolute number (e.g., Candidate A won by 5,000 votes) or as a percentage of the total votes cast (e.g., Candidate A won by a 5% margin). Understanding vote margins is important for analyzing election results and the level of support for different candidates or parties.",
